A RESOLUTION
To express sincere and heartfelt condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
upon the passing of Troy Carter, general manager, and the voice for the Chicken
Shack restaurant.
WHEREAS, it is with deep regret and profound sorrow that the citizens of Baton
Rouge, Louisiana, the customers and staff of Chicken Shack, and people worldwide, learned
that God Almighty in his infinite wisdom called Troy Carter to eternal rest on May 25, 2026,
at the age of sixty-nine; and
WHEREAS, Troy was born on November 15, 1956 in Checotah, Oklahoma and
enjoyed fishing, watching western shows and movies, reading the Bible, and dancing; and
WHEREAS, many described the fun loving man as the general manager who worked
for over forty-six years and became the voice of Chicken Shack located at 413 North
Acadian Thruway, Baton Rouge, LA; and
WHEREAS, Troy, in answer to his pastor's challenge to the congregation, "to take
the ministry to the marketplace" decided that when he records the restaurant's daily menu
on the answering machine, he would add an inspirational message at the end; and
WHEREAS, for seventeen years, the inspirational messages became so popular that
people from all over the world were known to call in just to listen to Troy's messages, which
always addressed the issues of the moments such as violence, bad weather, lost souls, and
asked people to pray about those problems; and
WHEREAS, Troy regularly reminded people of positive things such as the need to
count their blessings, to pray continually for each other, to worship God, and give Him
praise, honor, and glory; and
