WHEREAS, Chicken Shack's staff grieved him by posting on social media "It is with
the heaviest heart that we inform our friends and family that our dear family member Troy
Carter has gone to be with the Father. We are praying for strength and peace to all the
family, friends, and all the people this man has touched in his life. He will be sincerely
missed and never forgotten"; and
WHEREAS, Chicken Shack's staff tribute to Troy Carter, well describes the feelings
of so many that he impacted as he "took the ministry to the marketplace" per his pastor's
challenge.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby express sincere and heartfelt condolences upon the passing of Troy Carter,
general manager, and the voice for Chicken Shack restaurant on North Acadian Thruway,
and extend enduring appreciation for the tremendous pride and honor that his memories will
forever bring to one of the oldest restaurant's in Baton Rouge, Louisiana.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Troy
Carter's family and the North Acadian Thruway Chicken Shack.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
